---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="From Curiosity to Code: My Journey Into the World of Computers">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[72ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono">
        <span>Essay</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>August 2025</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        From Curiosity to Code: My Journey Into the World of Computers
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        "Build things that still make sense a decade later."
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      <p>
        Every journey begins with a spark of curiosity.
        Mine started when I was in third standard.
        At that time, computers were rare in households.
        Owning one felt like a luxury.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        My first exposure was simple observation.
        I watched how software responded to user inputs.
        The ability to direct a machine fascinated me.
        This curiosity soon turned into a desire to build.
      </p>

      <p>
        I began learning programming fundamentals step by step.
        I spent hours understanding syntax and logic.
        Each solved bug built my confidence.
        I realized that software is a medium for craftsmanship.
      </p>

      <p>
        Today, my focus remains on building reliable systems.
        I continue to explore operating systems and networking.
        The luxury is no longer just owning a computer.
        The luxury is having the capacity to understand them.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Article Footer: Network of Knowledge -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-8 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.08)] pt-12 mt-8">
      
      <!-- Related Links -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-sm">
        
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <h4 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-medium">Further Reading</h4>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/writing/why-i-started-writing" class="text-[#2563EB] hover:underline">
                Why I Started Writing
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <h4 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-medium">Referenced Books</h4>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/reading" class="text-[#2563EB] hover:underline">
                Steve Jobs (Biography)
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>

    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
